x4freetext: MSU/NSCL A1200 fragment separator.
A 90Zr target of thickness 1.0 mg/cm2. (The target
thickness was such that the maximum energy loss of
the beam in traversing the target was 0.26
MeV/nucleon.)
The 300 mm2 Si detectors were 50, 50 and
300 microm thick, respectively
Time of flight was measured between a
parallel plate avalanche counter and a microchannel
plate detector positioned at the first dispersive
image and at the focal plane, respectively, and
separated by a distance of 14 m.
